.TH "__stm_source_link_drop" 9 "__stm_source_link_drop" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__stm_source_link_drop \- detach stm_source from an stm device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __stm_source_link_drop
.BI "(struct stm_source_device *src "  ","
.BI "struct stm_device *stm "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "src" 12
stm_source device
.IP "stm" 12
stm device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If \fIstm\fP is \fIsrc\fP::link, disconnect them from one another and put the
reference on the \fIstm\fP device.

Caller must hold stm::link_mutex.
